{"type":"message","id":"cb9d23ba","parentId":"177629a8","timestamp":"2026-03-23T19:38:52.362Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9hicjojxwnv1_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 152846\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: tic/classifier.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the key pending item is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is the key breakthrough - causal structure IS invariant structure. The next action should be implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that:\r\n   - Analyzes pulse logs for invariant vs variant content\r\n   - Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measures accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and create the TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and validate against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants and measure classification/prediction accuracy against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$lookback = 20,\r\n    [double]$threshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$logFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \"logs\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $lookback\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($f in $logFiles) {\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $f.Name\r\n        Content = Get-Content $f.FullName -Raw\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize and extract features\r\nfunction Get-Features {\r\n    param([string]$text)\r\n    $tokens = $text -split '\\W+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 3 }\r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Find invariants across all pulses (appear in >threshold fraction)\r\n$allTokens = @{}\r\nforeach ($p in $pulses) {\r\n    $features = Get-Features $p.Content\r\n    foreach ($t in $features) {\r\n        if ($allTokens.ContainsKey($t)) { $allTokens[$t]++ }\r\n        else { $allTokens[$t] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariantTokens = @($allTokens.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value / $lookback -ge $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key })\r\n$variantTokens = @($allTokens.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value / $lookback -lt $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key })\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Analysis: $lookback pulses, ?=$threshold ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariants found: $($invariantTokens.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variants found: $($variantTokens.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Classify each pulse\r\n$correct = 0\r\n$total = 0\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $features = Get-Features $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    $invRatio = ($features | Where-Object { $invariantTokens -contains $_ }).Count / $features.Count\r\n    $predicted = if ($invRatio -ge 0.5) { \"invariant\" } else { \"variant\" }\r\n    \r\n    # Actual next pulse classification\r\n    $nextFeatures = Get-Features $pulses[$i+1].Content\r\n    $nextInvRatio = ($nextFeatures | Where-Object { $invariantTokens -contains $_ }).Count / $nextFeatures.Count\r\n    $actual = if ($nextInvRatio -ge 0.5) { \"invariant\" } else { \"variant\" }\r\n    \r\n    if ($predicted -eq $actual) { $correct++ }\r\n    $total++\r\n}\r\n\r\n$accuracy = if ($total -gt 0) { $correct / $total * 100 } else { 0 }\r\nWrite-Host \"Next-pulse prediction accuracy: $([math]::Round($accuracy, 1))%\"\r\n\r\n# Output results\r\n$result = [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n    Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n    Lookback = $lookback\r\n    Threshold = $threshold\r\n    InvariantCount = $invariantTokens.Count\r\n    VariantCount = $variantTokens.Count\r\n    PredictionAccuracy = $accuracy\r\n    MeetsCriteria = $accuracy -ge 60\r\n}\r\n$result | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File \"logs/tic_results.json\" -Append\r\nWrite-Host \"Results saved to logs/tic_results.json\"\r\nfile: src/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n`\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 15:29:03"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":829,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 152846\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: tic/classifier.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the key pending item is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight is the key breakthrough - causal structure IS invariant structure. The next action should be implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. First understand what pulse logs exist\r\n2. Create a TIC classifier that:\r\n   - Analyzes pulse logs for invariant vs variant content\r\n   - Predicts next pulse content from invariants\r\n   - Measures accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me check what pulse logs exist and create the TIC implementation.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight provides a clear path: implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) to classify invariant vs variant content across pulse logs and validate against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the TIC classifier script that will analyze pulse logs for invariants and measure classification/prediction accuracy against the success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$lookback = 20,\r\n    [double]$threshold = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$logFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path \"logs\" -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name -Descending | Select-Object -First $lookback\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($f in $logFiles) {\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        File = $f.Name\r\n        Content = Get-Content $f.FullName -Raw\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Tokenize and extract features\r\nfunction Get-Features {\r\n    param([string]$text)\r\n    $tokens = $text -split '\\W+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 3 }\r\n    return $tokens\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Find invariants across all pulses (appear in >threshold fraction)\r\n$allTokens = @{}\r\nforeach ($p in $pulses) {\r\n    $features = Get-Features $p.Content\r\n    foreach ($t in $features) {\r\n        if ($allTokens.ContainsKey($t)) { $allTokens[$t]++ }\r\n        else { $allTokens[$t] = 1 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n$invariantTokens = @($allTokens.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value / $lookback -ge $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key })\r\n$variantTokens = @($allTokens.GetEnumerator() | Where-Object { $_.Value / $lookback -lt $threshold } | ForEach-Object { $_.Key })\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Analysis: $lookback pulses, ?=$threshold ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Invariants found: $($invariantTokens.Count)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Variants found: $($variantTokens.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# Classify each pulse\r\n$correct = 0\r\n$total = 0\r\nfor ($i = 0; $i -lt $pulses.Count - 1; $i++) {\r\n    $features = Get-Features $pulses[$i].Content\r\n    $invRatio = ($features | Where-Object { $invariantTokens -contains $_ }).Count / $features.Count\r\n    $predicted = if ($invRatio -ge 0.5) { \"invariant\" } else { \"variant\" }\r\n    \r\n    # Actual next pulse classification\r\n    $nextFeatures = Get-Features $pulses[$i+1].Content\r\n    $nextInvRatio = ($nextFeatures | Where-Object { $invariantTokens -contains $_ }).Count / $nextFeatures.Count\r\n    $actual = if ($nextInvRatio -ge 0.5) { \"invariant\" } else { \"variant\" }\r\n    \r\n    if ($predicted -eq $actual) { $correct++ }\r\n    $total++\r\n}\r\n\r\n$accuracy = if ($total -gt 0) { $correct / $total * 100 } else { 0 }\r\nWrite-Host \"Next-pulse prediction accuracy: $([math]::Round($accuracy, 1))%\"\r\n\r\n# Output results\r\n$result = [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n    Timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\r\n    Lookback = $lookback\r\n    Threshold = $threshold\r\n    InvariantCount = $invariantTokens.Count\r\n    VariantCount = $variantTokens.Count\r\n    PredictionAccuracy = $accuracy\r\n    MeetsCriteria = $accuracy -ge 60\r\n}\r\n$result | ConvertTo-Json | Out-File \"logs/tic_results.json\" -Append\r\nWrite-Host \"Results saved to logs/tic_results.json\"\r\nfile: src/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n`\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 15:29:03","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774294732359}}
